# Go build output
/fido
*.test
*.out
vendor/

# The extracted program is GENERATED from the .v by `make extract` (a side effect of compiling main.v),
# canonicalised with gofmt, and its runtime behaviour is pinned by expected_output.txt.  It is NOT committed:
# `make check` regenerates + verifies it, so it can never go stale unnoticed, and there is no 58 KB generated
# artifact tracked in source.  Root-anchored so it only matches the repo-root program file.
/main.go

# Environment
.env

# Negtest harness scratch output (a negtest that wrongly EXTRACTS leaves this; run.sh cleans it)
/neg_out.go

# GoPrint.v's [Extraction "printer.ml"] drops these in the repo ROOT as a side effect of
# `rocq c -Q . Fido GoPrint.v`; the COMMITTED copy is plugin/printer.ml (moved there by `make printer`).
# Root-anchored so plugin/printer.ml stays tracked.
/printer.ml
/printer.mli

# `make emit-demo` intermediates: emitdemo/emit_demo.{ml,mli} are extracted from emitdemo/emit_demo.v; the
# OCaml build files + writer executable are transient.  The COMMITTED emit-demo files are
# emitdemo/emit_demo.v, emitdemo/write_emit.ml, and the certificate-gated output emitdemo/spine_demo.go.
/emitdemo/emit_demo.ml
/emitdemo/emit_demo.mli
/emitdemo/*.cmi
/emitdemo/*.cmo
/_emit_writer
# spine_demo.go is GENERATED on demand by `make emit-demo` (its exact bytes are already pinned + gate-checked
# by GoEmit.demo_emit_bytes); not committed, so it can never go stale unnoticed.
/emitdemo/spine_demo.go

# Rocq build artifacts — .v and .go sources are checked in, these are not
*.glob
*.vo
*.vok
*.vos
*.vio
*.aux
.*.aux
.lia.cache
.nia.cache
.coq-native/
_build/
